structs a network composed of monitors and editors to observe and alter the incoming response. <p> For example, a generator can stipulate that it is invoked only when the current request is for a fake document on a nonexisting server such as http://_wbi/usermodel/query as in Figure 6 <ref> (Barrett, Maglio & Kellem 1996) </ref>. WBI uses its monitors to build a user model (which stores a users past history) and uses its generators and editors to predict a users interests and needs.
